import json import sys import traceback import re from java.nio.charset import StandardCharsets from org.apache.commons.io import IOUtils from org.apache.nifi.processor.io import StreamCallback from org.python.core.util import StringUtil
class TransformCallback(StreamCallback): def __init__(self): pass
def process(self, inputStream, outputStream): try: text = IOUtils.toString(inputStream, StandardCharsets.UTF_8) data = json.loads(text) data.pop(0) i = 0 for i in range(len(data) - 1): data[i]['Price'] = float(re.sub(',', '', data[i]['Price'])) data[i]['Open'] = float(re.sub(',', '', data[i]['Open'])) data[i]['High'] = float(re.sub(',', '', data[i]['High'])) data[i]['Low'] = float(re.sub(',', '', data[i]['Low'])) data[i]['Change'] = float(re.sub('%', '', data[i]['Change'])) if data[i]['Vol'][-1] == 'K': data[i]['Vol'] = int(float(re.sub('K', '', data[i]['Vol'])) * 1000) elif data[i]['Vol'][-1] == 'M': data[i]['Vol'] = int(float(re.sub('M', '', data[i]['Vol'])) * 1000000) i = i + 1 json_string = json.dumps(data) outputStream.write(bytearray(json_string.encode('utf-8'))) except: traceback.print_exc(file=sys.stdout) raise
flowFile = session.get() if flowFile != None: flowFile = session.write(flowFile, TransformCallback())
# Finish by transferring the FlowFile to an output relationship session.transfer(flowFile, REL_SUCCESS) session.commit()
